# Fix Dexie "utf8: invalid string" sync error

One or more messages with corrupt encoding are causing the entire chat synchronization to fail. I will implement a "resilient sync" strategy that attempts to process messages individually if the bulk process fails, skipping any that are unrecoverable.

## Proposed Changes

### [Chat Sync Layer](file:///c:/Users/elink/./gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/sync.ts)

#### [MODIFY] [sync.ts](file:///c:/Users/elink/./gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/sync.ts)

- Wrap the `bulkPut` operation in a try-catch.
- On failure, attempt to [put](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/CustomFilePicker.tsx#307-324) messages one by one.
- On individual failure, skip the corrupt message, log it, and continue with the rest of the sync.
- This ensures that a single bad message doesn't prevent other messages from appearing in the UI.

#### [MODIFY] [db.ts](file:///c:/Users/elink/./gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/db.ts)

- Update [sanitizeMessage](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/db.ts#18-34) to be even more defensive, ensuring that all fields are strictly strings and not just "not null".

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  Verify that with the new logic, the sync process completes even if the console shows `[Sync] Failed to insert corrupt message`.
2.  Observe that "good" messages continue to stream in even if a "bad" one exists.
3.  Check the console for clear diagnostic messages about skipped items.
